jobs.body_en:
Ad title:
Lawyer
Provided By:
Batumi International Airport
Published:
15 January
/
Deadline:
31 January
Batumi Airport LLC
(member of ADP Group), a managing company of Batumi International Airport, is pleased to announce a vacancy for a
Lawyer
(Junior).
Responsibilities:
** Draft the standard and non-standard agreements, ensure their compliance with the appropriate legislation;
** Organize the process of signing of agreements;
** Distribute the signed agreements to relevant units of the Company and counterparties;
** Register agreements in a Contract registry upon necessity and make relevant records and updates in it;
** Prepare official letters to counterparties, state authorities or other individuals or entities on legal matters;
** Prepare internal power of attorney documents on behalf of the management of the Company for employees;
** Assist the Lawyers of the Company in court litigation cases upon necessity;
** Assist the lawyers of the Company in organizing notary, public registry, apostille etc. procedures, including visits at appropriate offices;
** Assist the lawyers of the Company in data & legislation research for legal compliance purposes, including preparing legal memos and analysis;
** Assist the lawyers of the Company in their other formal and legal activities.
Qualification Requirements:
** University degree in Law;
** Minimum 1 year of experience in legal activities for private entities;
** Foreign languages: Good knowledge of English is mandatory (ability of working on documents, written and oral communication).
** Computer Literacy; Knowledge of MS Office - Good knowledge of Word and Outlook; Elementary user knowledge of Excel.
Skills and Abilities
** High Sense of responsibility;
** Punctuality, motivation, flexibility and detail-orientation;
** Ability to work with deadlines in multitask environment;
** Time-management skills, self-organized and result-oriented personality;
** Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
** Tolerance to multi-national and multi-language environment.
Main Terms and Benefits:
** Working schedule - full time, 5 days a week, 8 hour working day
** Salary - negotiable, depending on experience, qualification, skills and motivation
** Health insurance package
** Free meal once a day;
** Free transportation service to and from the job, from several central points in the city.
If you meet with the requirements above and are eager to work in Batumi International Airport, please submit your CV to the following E-mail:
hrbus@tav.aero
no later than
31.01.2026
.
Only short-listed candidates will be invited to the interview and testing.
Please, note, that knowledge of languages, computer literacy and skills of working on formal documents may be examined during the interview.
Personal data notice:
The purpose of processing personal data at Batumi Airport LLC is to manage applications in view of possible pre-selection and further recruitment. All personal data collected will only be used for this purpose and will in no case be transmitted to any third party without applicants` consent. Information submitted by applicant will be registered in Company`s database for one year.

